title._content: [Portrait of Nat King Cole, Paramount Theater, New York, N.Y., ca. Nov. 1946] (LOC)

description._content: Gottlieb, William P., 1917-, photographer. [Portrait of Nat King Cole, Paramount Theater, New York, N.Y., ca. Nov. 1946] 1 negative : b&w ; 2 1/4 x 2 1/4 in. Caption from Down Beat: Jumped push-bike and pedaled to Paramount to corner King Cole & Stan Kenton. Said Cole, spelling message in Morse code on educated piano Notes: Gottlieb Collection Assignment No. 084 Reference print available in Music Division, Library of Congress. Purchase William P. Gottlieb Forms part of: William P. Gottlieb Collection (Library of Congress). In: "Posin'," Down Beat, v. 13, no. 23 (Nov. 4, 1946), p. 3. Subjects: Cole, Nat King, 1917-1965 Jazz musicians--1940-1950. Pianists--1940-1950. Jazz singers--1940-1950. Paramount Theater Format: Portrait photographs--1940-1950. Film negatives--1940-1950.
